1. copy other/nova-dcns.conf to /etc/nova/nova-dcns.conf
2. copy other/*.yaml.sample to /etc/nova/*.yaml
3. copy other/flags.py to $src/nova/flags.py
4. copy other/db-api.py to $src/nova/db/api.py
5. copy other/db-sqlalchemy-api.py to $src/nova/db/sqlalchemy/api.py and other/db-sqlalchemy-models.py to $src/nova/db/sqlalchemy/models.py
6. run service: ./bin/nova-dcns
7. copy cli.py to bin/dcns_cli
8. run ./bin/dcns_cli, examples:
	./bin/dcns-cli create projectA 100Mbps 101 bespin102:eth1 bespin105:eth1
	./bin/dcns-cli show projectA 
	./bin/dcns-cli remove projectA

9 copy other/network-manager.py to $src/nova/network/manager.py
   run ./bin/nova-compute /etc/nova/nova.conf


-----> service start patch 

ln -s /lib/init/upstart-job /etc/init.d/nova-dcns
cp nova-dcns /usr/bin/nova-dcns
cp other/init-nova-dcns.conf /etc/init/nova-dcns.conf
cp other/035_dcns.py $src/nova/db/sqlalchemy/migration_repo/versions/0xx_dcns.py
nova-manage db sync
service nova-dcns start

----> openflow control

setup ssh key for ssh access (for user nova)
try manual ssh login from user nova


-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

A patching package for Nova Lucid located at other/nova-lucid-patch.

This is manual patch of for systems installed with release tagged 2011.2-0ubuntu0ppa1~lucid1.

